\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Quasipotential $V(\lambda ) = \DOTSI \intop \ilimits@ _\lambda ^1 \!\sqrt  {G_{\lambda \lambda }}\,d\lambda '$ on coherence space, measuring the accumulated Fubini--Study distance to the classical frame. The steep walls at both endpoints reflect the divergent metric (geometric fragility of coherence, rigidity of classicality), while the gentle intermediate slope identifies a crossover plateau where large increases in distinguishability produce only small movements in projective Hilbert space. The global minimum at $\lambda = 1$ (pointer basis) represents the stable classical frame.}}{7}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:quasipotential}{{4}{7}{Quasipotential $V(\lambda ) = \int _\lambda ^1 \!\sqrt {\Gll }\,d\lambda '$ on coherence space, measuring the accumulated Fubini--Study distance to the classical frame. The steep walls at both endpoints reflect the divergent metric (geometric fragility of coherence, rigidity of classicality), while the gentle intermediate slope identifies a crossover plateau where large increases in distinguishability produce only small movements in projective Hilbert space. The global minimum at $\lambda = 1$ (pointer basis) represents the stable classical frame}{figure.4}{}}
