\newlabel{fig:cr_vs_standard}{{5}{7}{Comparison of the normalized \CR {} geometric transition $V(\lambda )/V(0)$ (solid, red) with standard QM visibility $\mathcal {V} = \sqrt {1-\lambda ^2}$ (dashed, blue). The CR curve drops faster through the crossover region due to the metric structure, producing a testable deviation $\Delta \approx 0.24$ at intermediate~$\lambda $}{figure.5}{}}
